---Overview---

This repository contains the design, justification, and documentation for a secure network architecture configuration, completed as part of a course on computer systems security. 
The goal was to identify necessary security components and configure them in a layered defense model to protect a conceptual computer system.

 1. Proposed Security Configuration Diagram

The diagram below illustrates the perimeter defense and internal security segmentation, ensuring all external traffic passes through the primary security control point.

